<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_b3973e7a-f6bb-487a-ae1f-8d337a07aefa" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 1a"/><facet building="Class 1b"/><facet building="Class 10a"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>E4D3</sptc><title id="_cbc60e93-9255-4d1e-adfb-78fee122abdc">Measurement of distance</title><archive-num>2019: E4.3</archive-num><subclause id="_b3a5d3fa-817f-4954-8e77-5f1206520d84" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_c9c9ddb9-913f-4162-be60-3ade0ad443cc">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Distances, other than vertical rise, must be measured along the shortest path of travel whether by straight lines, curves or a combination of both.</p></subclause></clause>